Kaizer Chiefs , a South African
Premier League soccer team, have signed an agreement to play
their home matches at Soccer City in Johannesburg for the next
five years, Business Day reported, citing Jacques Grobbelaar,
executive chairman of Stadium Management SA, which manages the
stadium in Soweto where the  World Cup  final was played in July
2010.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
